 Protesters marched to the provincial legislature to submit a memorandum of demands to the MEC for public works, Gillion Mashego.  On Tuesday morning people gathered outside Makro and walked to the legislature. ALSO READ:MEC of Health and Public Works switched In their statement, the protesters stated that the march was to address the corruption involving tenders for scholar transport, to demand an investigation into various projects such as the R500 million given to the Mpumalanga Growth Development Agency (MEGA), the R2 billion for the hospitals in Mpumalanga, and MEGA being appointed as the implementing agency for all water projects, despite the fact it had no previous experience. PHOTOS: